topics.body:
Finally started reading Daily Life with Monster Girl, and I really should have started sooner considering that I adore sexy monster folk.

Anyways its really funny, cute, sexy, everything you want from a harem comedy series recently.

Also it does something I really like, specifically it gives us a male protagonist to one of these stories who isn't a complete fucking putz. He really comes off as a relatively ordinary guy stuck in a really strange situation as opposed to making me scream "what the fuck is wrong with you, you muppet?!" over and over again, which is what most harem comedies cause me to do.

Also its the only one I can think of where a female character reacts badly to the male accidentally doing something that might be considered perverted and then apologizing for freaking out and hitting him.

All in all a very pleasant read so far.
